LEETCODE - 1 : TWO SUM:
💡 Intuition

We need to find two numbers such that:

nums[i] + nums[j] = target

Instead of checking all pairs (which is slow), we can:

For each number, calculate its complement:
complement = target - nums[i]
Then check if this complement was seen before

###This avoids nested loops and makes it fast

⚙️ Approach
Use a hash map (dictionary) to store:
value → index
Traverse the array:
Compute complement = target - nums[i]
If complement exists in hashmap → return indices
Else store current value with index


 #####CODE
class Solution:
    def twoSum(self, nums: List[int], target: int) -> List[int]:
        hashmap={}
        for i in range(len(nums)):
            y=target-nums[i]
            if y in hashmap:
                return [hashmap[y],i]
            hashmap[nums[i]]=i
